between the circle

00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:46.450 align:middle line:84%
and the horizontal
lines here and here.

00:06:46.450 --> 00:06:49.030 align:middle line:84%
Now, obviously, no one works
at this level of precision just

00:06:49.030 --> 00:06:50.558 align:middle line:90%
to hide some triangles.

00:06:50.558 --> 00:06:52.100 align:middle line:10%
There's got to be
more going on here.

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:59.560 align:middle line:84%
We must measure them,
"By G," "to be," E, NE.

00:06:59.560 --> 00:07:01.360 align:middle line:84%
During the Renaissance,
the letter G

00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:03.370 align:middle line:84%
was often used on
maps and emblems

00:07:03.370 --> 00:07:05.950 align:middle line:84%
to indicate the
globe or the Earth.

00:07:05.950 --> 00:07:08.440 align:middle line:84%
And, anciently, the
Pythagoreans used the letter G

00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:11.110 align:middle line:90%
to mean geometry itself.

00:07:11.110 --> 00:07:13.600 align:middle line:90%
They're measuring the Earth.

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:18.340 align:middle line:84%
